Aligning Sales and Marketing Around Pipeline Reality
Sales forecasting challenges often stem from misalignment between sales and marketing. Sales says pipeline is strong. Finance sees leading indicators that suggest otherwise. Marketing reports engagement levels that don't match sales forecast confidence.

This misalignment destroys forecast accuracy. It also wastes budget on campaigns targeting accounts sales has already disqualified.

Creating Unified Pipeline View:

Sales and marketing should agree on what constitutes qualified pipeline. This means:

Is this account actively showing buying signals? Has marketing engagement with this account indicated buying interest? Do we have visibility into their buying committee? Have they downloaded buyer-focused content or visited pricing pages? Are they comparing us to competitors?

When marketing and sales agree on these criteria before deals enter the forecast, accuracy improves immediately. Marketing stops generating low-quality leads. Sales focuses on accounts showing genuine intent. Pipeline composition becomes predictable and reliable.

Implementation Framework:

Work with marketing to define buyer personas and corresponding intent signals. Create a shared dashboard showing pipeline accounts, their engagement status, and intent signal strength. Meet monthly to align on account prioritization and campaign timing. Measure how accounts move through pipeline stages and adjust sales and marketing activities based on what you learn.

